.TH _PRINTF 3 "October 2025" "Holberton School" "Library Functions Manual"
.SH NAME
_printf \- simplified printf function
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include "main.h"
.PP
.BI "int _printf(const char *format, ...);"
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B _printf
function produces output according to a format string.
It is a simplified version of the C standard library function
.BR printf (3).

The function writes output to the standard output (file descriptor 1).
Output is written using the low-level
.BR write (2)
system call.

The
.I format
string is composed of zero or more directives:
ordinary characters (not %), which are copied unchanged to the output,
and conversion specifiers, each introduced by a '%' character.

Supported conversion specifiers are:
.TP
.B %c
Prints a single character.
.TP
.B %s
Prints a string. If the string pointer is NULL, "(null)" is printed.
.TP
.B %d, %i
Prints a signed decimal integer.
.TP
.B %%
Prints a literal percent sign.

.SH RETURN VALUE
Upon success,
.B _printf
returns the number of characters printed (excluding the terminating null byte).
On failure, it returns \-1.

.SH EXAMPLES
Print a simple string:
.nf
    _printf("Hello, world!\\n");
.fi
.PP
Print characters and numbers:
.nf
    _printf("Character: %c, Number: %d\\n", 'A', 123);
.fi
.PP
Print a string with percent signs:
.nf
    _printf("100%% Complete\\n");
.fi

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR printf (3),
.BR write (2)

.SH AUTHOR
Written as part of the Holberton School printf project.
